{"atom_id":"ig34_p0261_a001","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":261,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.7 Microbiology Domains","atom_type":"SENTENCE","verbatim":"The RELSPEC table shows the relationship of the parent sample to its aliquots. The LEVEL variable indicates that the sample has been subsampled. The original parent sample is always LEVEL=\"1\". An aliquot of the sample would be LEVEL=\"2\". If the aliquot was further split, that subsample would be LEVEL=\"3\".","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_round5_inline","ts":"2026-04-27T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0261_a002","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":261,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.7 Microbiology Domains","atom_type":"LIST_ITEM","verbatim":"Row 1: Shows the original collected (parent) sample. The PARENT variable is left blank to indicate that this is the highest level sample.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_round5_inline","ts":"2026-04-27T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0261_a003","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":261,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.7 Microbiology Domains","atom_type":"LIST_ITEM","verbatim":"Rows 2-6: Show the relationship of each aliquot in the BE domain to the parent sample. PARENT is populated with the REFID value of the parent sample, indicating that the sample with REFID=\"100\" is the parent of these samples. LEVEL=\"2\" indicates that these aliquots are subsamples of the original (LEVEL=\"1\") sample.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_round5_inline","ts":"2026-04-27T00:00:00Z"}}
