{"atom_id":"ig34_p0261_a012","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":261,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.5.7 Microbiology Domains","atom_type":"SENTENCE","verbatim":"Results from detection tests performed on samples are represented in the MB domain. The sputum sample was aliquoted 5 times. Three of these aliquots underwent detection testing using 3 separate tests: 1 for acid-fast bacillus (AFB), 1 for M. tuberculosis complex, and 1 for M. tuberculosis.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_round5_inline","ts":"2026-04-27T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0261_a013","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":261,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.5.7 Microbiology Domains","atom_type":"SENTENCE","verbatim":"MBTESTCD/MBTEST represents the organism being investigated, MBMETHOD represents the testing method, and MBREFID represents which aliquot was tested. The variable MBTSTDTL is used to provide further description of the test performed in producing the MB result. In addition to detection, MBTSTDTL can be used to represent specific attributes (e.g., quantifiable and semi-quantifiable results of the culture) as well as qualitative details about the culture (e.g., colony color, morphology).","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_round5_inline","ts":"2026-04-27T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0261_a014","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":261,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.5.7 Microbiology Domains","atom_type":"LIST_ITEM","verbatim":"Row 1: Shows a test targeting the presence or absence of AFB using a stain. The MBSPCCND shows that the sample used in the test was concentrated. MBGRPID can be used to connect the detection record with the corresponding AFB quantification results shown in row 2.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_round5_inline","ts":"2026-04-27T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0261_a015","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":261,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.5.7 Microbiology Domains","atom_type":"LIST_ITEM","verbatim":"Row 2: Shows a categorical result for an AFB test using a stain. MBORRES contains a result based on a CDC AFB quantification scale. The name of the scale used is represented as a supplemental qualifier. MBREFID indicates which aliquot the procedure was performed upon and MBGRPID is used to connect the AFB quantification record to the detection record in row 1.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_round5_inline","ts":"2026-04-27T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0261_a016","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":261,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.5.7 Microbiology Domains","atom_type":"LIST_ITEM","verbatim":"Row 3: Shows a test targeting the presence or absence of M. tuberculosis complex using a genotyping method. Details about the assay can be found in the Device Identifiers (DI) domain. The value in SPDEVID links the genotype result to the assay information in the DI domain. The microbial detection certainty is represented as a supplemental qualifier. Because genotyping was used, the detection is considered to be definitive.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_round5_inline","ts":"2026-04-27T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0261_a017","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":261,"page_region":"bottom","parent_section":"§6.3.5.7 Microbiology Domains","atom_type":"LIST_ITEM","verbatim":"Row 4: Shows a test targeting the presence or absence of M. tuberculosis performed on a solid culture. The medium type and microbial detection certainty are represented as supplemental qualifier. Because genotyping was not used, the detection is considered to be presumptive. The culture start and stop dates are represented in BE and are connected to the culture results via BELNKID and MBLNKGRP. MBGRPID is used to connect the detection record in MB with the corresponding culture characteristics shown in rows 5-7.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_round5_inline","ts":"2026-04-27T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0261_a018","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":261,"page_region":"bottom","parent_section":"§6.3.5.7 Microbiology Domains","atom_type":"LIST_ITEM","verbatim":"Row 5: Shows a colony-forming unit (CFU) count from a solid culture. The MBORRES value represents the actual colony count from this plate. However, the sample that was spread on this plate represented a 100-fold dilution from the original subject sample. This information is represented in the Dilution Factor supplemental qualifier (MBDILFCT), whose value = 10^-2 (1/100th). In order to enable more straightforward pooling of CFU data, a simple integer result (14700) is used in MBSTRESC/N, and MBSTRESU=\"CFU/mL\". The medium type for the solid culture is also represented as a supplemental qualifier.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_round5_inline","ts":"2026-04-27T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0262_a001","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":262,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.7 Microbiology Domains","atom_type":"LIST_ITEM","verbatim":"Row 6: Shows the standardized colony count category based on a CDC M. tuberculosis colony quantification scale. The quantification scale used and the medium type for the solid culture are represented as supplemental qualifiers.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_round5_inline","ts":"2026-04-27T00:01:00Z"}}
